Protocol.text: For derivation at post implantation stages, the late epiblast layer of embryos at pre- or early gastrulation stages (5.5 dpc or 6.5 dpc) was separated from extra-embryonic tissues by microdissection using Cell Dissociation Buffer (Invitrogen) at 4 degrees C for 15-20 min. to promote dissociation of the layers. The resulting pure epiblast cell layers were then cultivated on fibronectin or fetal bovine serum (FBS) coated plates in chemically defined medium (CDM; Johansson and Wiles, 1995) supplemented with 20 ng/ml of Activin A and 12 ng/ml of FGF2. Johansson B.M. and Wiles M.V., Mol. Cell Biol., 1995, 15:141-151
Protocol.name: LV_EpiSC_GROWTH

Protocol.text: For feeder and Serum free culture, EpiSCs were grown in chemically defined medium (CDM; Johansson and Wiles, 1995) supplemented with Activin (10 ng/ml, RandD systems) and FGF2 (12 ng/ml, RandD systems). The composition of CDM was 50% IMDM (Gibco) plus 50% F12 NUT-MIX (Gibco), supplemented with 7 mg/ml of insulin (Roche), 15 mg/ml of transferrin (Roche), 450 mM of monothioglycerol (Sigma) and 5 mg/ml bovine serum albumin fraction V (Europabioproducts). Every 4 days, cells were harvested using 5 mg/ml collagenase IV (Gibco) or Accutase (BioWest) and then plated into plates (Costar) pre-coated with 15 mg/ml of human Fibronectin (Chemicon) for 20 minutes at 37C and then washed twice in PBS. Johansson, B. M. & Wiles, M. V., Mol. Cell Biol., 1995, 15:141-51
Protocol.name: LV_EpiSC_TREATMENT

Protocol.text: Extraction was performed as described in (Tietjen et al., 2003). Tietjen I. et al., Neuron, 2003, 38:161-175.
Protocol.name: LS_AMP_EXTRACT

Protocol.text: Selected amplified cDNA samples were fragmented and biotin end-labelled as described in (Tietjen et al., 2003). Tietjen I. et al., Neuron, Vol 38, 161-175.
Protocol.name: LS_AMP_LABEL

Protocol.text: Mouse epiblasts for transcriptional profiling were isolated by immunosurgery (Beddington et al., 2005) from B6/CBA F1 intercross embryos (at 6.5 - 7.5 days). Beddington et al., Manipulating the Mouse Embryo: A Laboratory Manual, 2nd ed., 2005, 191-272.
Protocol.name: LS_mEPI_GROWTH

Protocol.text: Mouse ESCs were generated from B6/CBA F1 intercross embryos by culturing E3.5 – E4.5 ICMs isolated by immunosurgery (Beddington et al., 2005) on irradiated MEF feeders in ES cell medium with LIF added. After 6 passages, populations of cells with ES morphology appeared. 4 lines were established (B6/CBA 1 – 4; B6/CBA 2, used here, arose after 4 passages). These were shown to be positive for the ES cell markers Oct4 and SSEA-1 by antibody labelling. RT-PCR showed expression of the characteristic ESC genes Esg1, fgf4, Rex-1 and nanog. Culture of B6/CBA2 cells in the absence of LIF in suspension led to cystic embryoid body formation. In adherent culture, these could undergo terminal differentiation to beating cardiomyocytes. In terms of antibody labelling, marker gene expression and behaviour on removal of LIF, the B6/CBA lines behaved exactly like the control D3 and CGR8 ESC lines. Beddington, R., et al. Manipulating the Mouse Embryo: A Laboratory Manual. 2nd ed. 2005, 191-272.
Protocol.name: LS_mESC_GROWTH

Protocol.text: Mouse inner cell masses (ICMs) for transcriptional profiling were isolated by immunosurgery (Beddington et al., 2005) from B6/CBA F1 intercross embryos (at 3.5 - 4.5 days). Beddington et al., Manipulating the Mouse Embryo: A Laboratory Manual, 2nd ed., 2005, 191-272.
Protocol.name: LS_mICM_GROWTH

Protocol.text: Affymetrix .CEL files were background corrected, normalized and summarized using the default parameters of the RMA model, as implemented in the "affy" package of the "Bioconductor" (www.bioconductor.org) suite of software for the "R" (www.r-project.org) statistical programming language. References: [RMA] Irizarry R.A. et al. Summaries of Affymetrix Genechip probe level data. Nucleic Acid Res. 31 E15 (2003). [Bioconductor] Gentleman R.C. et al. Bioconductor: open software development for computational biology and bioinformatics.Genome Biol. 2004;5(10):R80
Protocol.name: TRANPRTCL35169
